ARSET doc:readme.md 0 "# Redis Insight Prototype" "" "Welcome to the **Redis Insight** array viewer prototype." "It treats a Redis array as if it were a Markdown file — one row per line." "" "## Features" "" "- Browse keys with **filter** and *search*" "- Render escaped Markdown values inline" "- Expand context around every match" "- Aggregate numeric ranges (SUM, MIN, MAX)" "" "## Quick start" "" "Run a search with `MATCH \"bold\"` to find this line: **bold matters**." "Switch the combinator to `OR` to broaden the result set." "" "## Code example" "" "Use the CLI like this: `ARGREP doc:readme.md - + MATCH \"code\"`." "" "## A note on quotes" "" "> \"Caches are convenient, but only if they are correct.\"" "> — anon" "" "## Links" "" "Read more in the [Redis docs](https://redis.io/docs/)." "" "## Inline styles" "" "This row mixes **bold**, *italic*, and `code` in one place." "Even ~~strikethrough~~ via GitHub-Flavored Markdown works." "" "## TODO" "- [x] Render headings" "- [x] Render lists" "- [ ] Add table support test"
